('cse', 'Computer Science and Engg.', '<p>The Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the National Institute of Technology Jamshedpur, was formed in 1992. Since its inception, the department has always been recognized all over the country for its excellence. The Department has consistently produced quality professionals in the field of Computer Science &amp; Engineering and strived for excellence in research and development.</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision </span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Producing high quality industry ready Computer engineers to cater to the needs of the society.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To train young minds and to equip them with the best possible technical knowledge to meet the current and future demands of the industry, academia &amp; research.</li>\r\n<li>To create infrastructure, motivation and culture for the state of the art research work in the area of Computer Science &amp; Information Technology.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=CS01" class="pagelink"> Mr. Rajiv Ranjan Suman</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374097(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374101<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:hod.cse@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">hod.cse@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p> To be updated Soon </p>\r\n', '    <p>To be updated soon </p>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li>B.Tech (Hons.) in Computer Science &amp; Engg.</li>\n</ul>'),
('mca', 'Computer Applications', '<p>The Department of Computer Application at the National Institute of Technology Jamshedpur, was formed in 1987. Since its inception, the department has always been recognized all over the country for its excellence. The Department has consistently produced quality professionals in the field of Computer & Network and strived for excellence in research and development.</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=CA04" class="pagelink"> Dr. Danish Ali khan</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374116(HOD office), &nbsp;+91-657-2374120<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b>  <a href="mailto:hod.ca@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">hod.ca@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The department has following Laboratories:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>MCA Laboratory</li>\n</ul>', '<p><b>Research Areas:</b></p><ul><li>Software Engineering</li>\n<li>Parallel Computing</li>\n<li>Sensor Network Supply Chain Management</li>\n<li>Operation Research</li>\n<li>Operation Management</li>\n<li>Financial Management</li>\n<li>Computer Applications</li>\n</ul>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\n</p><ul><li><b>UG Program:</b>&nbsp;Not Available</li><li><a href="../academics/programmes/mca.php">MCA(Master In Computer Applications)</a></li>\n<li>Ph.D.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>'),
('chemistry', 'Chemistry', '<p>Department of Chemistry, National Institute of Technology, Jamshedpur was originally founded as Regional Institute of Technology in 1960 with the aim of nurturing talent and setting high standards of education and excellence. The Department offers instruction in General Chemistry and Engineering Chemistry to the students in different branches of Engineering students at B.Tech level. The Department started Post Graduate Programme (M.Tech) in Surface Science and Engineering since 1982. The department is equipped with various instruments. Besides teaching, the highly qualified and energetic faculty members of the Department have contribute a lot to elevate the prestige of the institute through their research activities of both basic and applied areas of chemistry.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p></br>\r\n<p><b> <span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" /></b></br>\r\n	<ul><li>To provide good fundamental concept of Chemistry applied to the Engineering field.</li>\r\n<li>	To introduce the importance of Chemistry in industry as well as in research field.</li>\r\n<li>	To study the importance of chemicals, chemical reactions, and physical phenomena, synthesis in higher study of Engineering.\r\n</li></ul></p>\r\n</br>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=CH02" class="pagelink"> Dr. Shailesh Kumar Prasad </a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374045(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374046 <br />\r\n<b>Email:</b>  <a href="mailto: hod.chem@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">hod.chem@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p><b>Laboratories:</br></b>B.Tech. & M.Tech. (Corrosion) Laboratories</p>', '<p><b>Research areas:</b><ul>\n<li>	Surface Chemistry</li>\n<li>	Environmental Chemistry</li>\n<li>	Analytical Chemistry</li>\n<li>	Corrosion Science</li>\n<li>	Biophysical & Analytical Chemistry</li>\n<li>	Self-assembly & Drug Delivery\n</li><li>	Nanomaterials</li>\n	<li>Water Research</li></ul></p>\n', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href="../department/mtechche.php">PG programs</a></b>:\n	<ul><li>2 year M.Tech in Surface Science and Engineering</li>\n    	\n    </ul>\n</li>\n\n</ul>'),
('civil', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The Department of Civil Engineering of National Institute of Technology (formerly Regional Institute of Technology) Jamshedpur was started with the inception of the institute itself in 1960. This core department had sanctioned strength of two Professors, two Assistant Professors and nine Lecturers.</p>\r\n<p>Present intake capacity of 90 students in each batch. The department has well qualified and experienced faculty members. Apart from teaching and research, all faculties are actively involving in training and other extra curricular activities for all round development of the Department.</p>\r\n<p>Faculties of this department are also undertaking design, testing &amp; consultancy works for various organizations leading to resource generation for the Institute. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=CE06" class="pagelink"> Dr. Anil Kumar Choudhary</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> + 91-657-2374123(HOD office),&nbsp;+ 91-657-2374003<br />\r\n<b>Fax:</b> + 91-657-2373246<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto: hod.civil@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">hod.civil@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p><b>The department has following Laboratories:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Structural Engineering Laboratory</li>\n<li>Concrete Laboratory</li>\n<li>Soli Mechanics Engineering Laboratory</li>\n<li>Geotechnical Engineering Laboratory</li>\n<li>Transportation Laboratory</li>\n<li>Survey Engineering Laboratory</li>\n<li>Environmental Engineering Laboratory</li>\n<li>CAD  Laboratory</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>The major equipments available are:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>UTM 1500 KN</li>\n<li>Ultra Sonic Pulse Velocity</li>\n<li>Flexural Testing Machine</li>\n<li>CBR Set-up</li>\n<li>Shear Strength Test Apparatus</li>\n<li>Digital Tri-axial Set-up</li>\n<li>Permeability Test Set-up</li>\n<li>Gas Chromotograph</li>\n<li>Spectrophoto meter</li>\n<li>COD &amp; DO meter</li>\n<li>Respiratory Dust Sampler</li>\n<li>pH meter</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Softwares:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>STRAP Suit Software Version 12.5</li>\n<li>PLAXIX 2D version 8.6</li>\n<li>Plax Flow version 1.4</li>\n<li>GGU Software (20 Users)</li>\n<li>GEO5  version 5.3 ( 5 Users)</li>\n<li>KANAL++ & Aqua ++</li>\n<li>CFX, SAP, ETABS, NASTRAN</li>\n<li>AUTODESK</li>\n<li>RAM</li>\n<li>AUTO-CAD</li>\n</ul>', '<p><b>Research Areas:</b></p><ul><li>Low cost Building materials\r\nPile Foundation</li>\r\n<li>Planning Management of Traffic Flow Pattern</li>\r\n<li>Slag Aggregate Cement Concrete</li>\r\n<li>Study on Reinforced Fly ash</li>\r\n<li>Design of Multistoried Structures</li>\r\n<li>Recycled Aggregate Concrete</li>\r\n<li>Water Quality Assessment</li>\r\n<li>Drinking Water supply network system development</li>\r\n<li>River Flood Flow Forecasting</li>\r\n<li>Earth Quake Impact Assessment\r\n</li></ul>', '\r\n<p>The department offers the following academic programs which have been designed in close interaction with industry and keeping in mind their current needs :-\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>UG Program:</b><ol><li>4 Years B.Tech. (Hons.) in Civil Engineering</li></ol>\r\n<li><b>PG Programs:</b></li><ol><li>2 Years M.Tech. in Structural Engineering</li><li>2 Years M.Tech in Water Resources and Environmental Engineering</li><li>Geo Technical Engineering</li><li>Infra Structural Engineering</li></ol><li>\r\n<b>Ph.D Programs:</b></li><ol><li>Ph.D. in relevant areas</li></ol>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>'),
('eee', 'Electrical &amp; Electronics Engineering', '<p>The Department of Electrical Engineering was started in 1960. The Department has been consistently producing quality Electrical Engineers since its inception  and is also involved in research and development activities.<br/>\r\nThe alumni of the department are well placed in both public and private sectors.<br/>\r\nIn addition to the UG program the department runs PG program in Power Systems and Ph.D. program in different areas of specialization.</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To be a centre for imparting world class education in the field of electrical engineering and conduct extensive and quality research and to propel innovations for the betterment of society.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To train young minds and to equip them with the best possible technical knowledge to meet the current and future demands of the industry, to recognize education and  research in close interaction with the industry and installing leadership qualities in  young men and women who enter the portals of the institute with sensitivity for social development and with an eye for growth in international perspective.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=EE03" class="pagelink"> Prof. Amar Nath Thakur</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-6572374093(HOD office),&nbsp; +91-657-6572374067 <br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="anthakur.ee@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">anthakur.ee@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>To be updated Soon \n...</p>', '<p>To be updated Soon ....</p>', '<p style="text-align:justify;">The department offers the following course(s) :-\n\n<ul>\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Electrical &amp; Electronics Engg.</li>\n<li><a href="../department/mtecheee.php">M.Tech. in Power System</a></li>\n<li>Ph.D.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>'),
('ece', 'Electronics & Communication Engineering', '<p>\r\nDepartment of Electronics and Communication Engineering was started in 1989. The department covers a host of subjects inclusive of electronic circuits, microprocessor, digital signal processing, analog communication, digital communication, mobile communication, VLSI, embedded systems, instrumentation ETC. The department has laboratories catering to all the subjects of studies. There are five research scholars working in different specializations under the groups Communication engineering, VLSI and embedded systems, Signal Processing, Instrumentation and soft computing. The Department has highly motivated faculty pool. \r\n</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Enhance the Student Learning Environment</li>\r\n<li>Commitment to Student Transformation and Success</li>\r\n<li>Transformational Scholarship</li>\r\n<li>Developing our Campus Community</li>\r\n<li>Resource Development</li>\r\n<li>Engagement with the Region</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Value creation through economic, social, and environmental development targeted to an increasing global and multicultural world.</li>\r\n<li>This leads an increasing number of academic and public service activities that involve and benefit the local community, the State of Jharkhand, India, and ultimately, the world. This continuing commitment to the public good, through a variety of outreach activities, is grounded in our tradition as a land-grant Institution.</li>\r\n<li>Original ideas that advance society through discovery, inquiry, innovation, research, transformational scholarship, and creative activities.</li>\r\n<li>Our ability to create value is dependent on discovering new knowledge and generating new ideas and expressions. The complex concerns of the 21st century cannot be addressed with existing knowledge and systems. Our aim is a dramatic increase in these activities, requiring the interaction between committed, diverse faculty, staff, students and community.</li>\r\n<li>Leadership through the preparation of capable and ethical leaders.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b> <a href="../faculty/index.php?id=EC02" class="pagelink">Dr. Shiva Nand Singh</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone: </b>+91 - 657 - 2374077(HOD office),&nbsp;+91 - 657 - 2374083\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Email: </b> <a href="mailto:snsingh.ece@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">snsingh.ece@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The Department has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</p>\n	<p>1.Basic electronics Lab.</p>\n	\n	<p>2.Analog electronics and Digital electronics Lab.</p>\n	\n	<p>3.Digital Signal Processing (DSP) Lab.</p> \n	<p>4.Analog & Digital communications Lab.</p>\n	<p>5.Microprocessor Lab.</p>\n	<p>6.Computer Networking Lab.</p>\n	<p>7.Industrial Electronics Lab.</p>\n	<p>8.VLSI Design and Embedded Systems Lab.</p>', '	<p><strong>Research areas:</strong></p>\r\n	<p>1.Solar Power Conversion Technology.</p>\r\n	<p>2.VLSI and Nanotechnology.</p>\r\n	<p>3.Research Specialisation subjects: Power electronics, Image processing, Embedded systems, Soft Computing & Instrumentation &Control.</p>\r\n	<p><strong>Conference and Short Term courses organized:</strong></p>\r\n	<p>National Workshop on VLSI & Embedded system based design in 2009 under co-ordination of various faculty members of ECE Department.</p>    ', '<p>The department offers the following academic programs which have been designed in close interaction with industry and keeping in mind their current needs :-\n<ul>\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering</li>\n<li><a href="../department/ece_m.tech.php">M.Tech. in VLSI design and embedded system</a></li>\n</ul>\n</p>'),
('maths', 'Mathematics', '<p>The Department was established in 1960.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=MTH01" class="pagelink"> Dr. S. Jha</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374058(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374059<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto: sjha.math@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">sjha.math@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>Not Available.</p>', '<p><b>Research Areas</b>:</p><ul><li>Numerical Analysis</li><li>Operations Research</li><li>Mathematical Modelling</li><li>Special Function</li><li>Fractional Calculus</li><li>Integral Calculus</li><li>Fuzzy Logic</li>', '<p>The Department offers following academic programs:</p><ul><li><b>UG Program:</b><br>Not Available.</li><li><b>PG Prgram:</b><br>  Not Available</li><li><b>Ph.D Program:</b><br>Available</li></ul>'),
('me', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Department of Mechanical Engineering was established in 1960 with the inception of Institute.</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To be a center of for imparting world class education in the field of Mechanical Engineering and conduct extensive and quality research and to propel innovations for the betterment of society.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To train young minds and to equip them with the best possible technical knowledge to meet the current and future demands of the industry, to recognize education and research in close interaction with the industry and instilling leadership qualities in young men and women who enter the portals of the Institute with sensitivity for social development and with an eye for growth in international perspective.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=ME10" class="pagelink"> Prof. (Dr.) R.K.Prasad</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374150(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374050 <br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:rkprasad.me@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">rkprasad.me@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The Department  has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Applied  Thermodynamics Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>CAD, CAM  &amp; CFD Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Fluid  Mechanics and Fluid Machinery Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Heat  Transfer laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Dynamics of  Machinery Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Metrology  Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Strength  of Materials Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Thermodynamics Model Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Automobile  Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Gas Dynamics  Laboratory</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p><b>Research areas</b>:</p>\n<ul><li>CFD, Heat Transfer, Solar Energy, Combined Power  Cycle, Gas Turbine, Tribology, Theory Machine, TPM, Pinch  Technology</li></ul>\n<p><b>Conference and Short Term courses organized</b>:</p>\n<ol><li>National  Conference on &ldquo;Modelling and Simulation of Heat Transfer and Fluid Flow&rdquo; was  organized during July 9-10,  2010.</li>\n	<li>Short Term  Training Program on &ldquo;Modelling and Simulation of Renewable Energy Systems&rdquo; was  organized during June18-22, 2012.</li>\n</ol>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>UG program</b>:\r\n	<ol><li>4 year B.Tech (H) in Mechanical Engineering</li></ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b><a href="../department/mtechmech.php">PG programs</a></b>:\r\n	<ol><li>2 year M.Tech in Computer Integrated Design and Manufacturing</li>\r\n    	<li>2 year M.Tech in Thermal and Fluids Engineering</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b>Ph.D programs</b>:\r\n	<ul><li>CFD, Heat Transfer, Solar Energy, Combined Power Cycle, Gas Turbine, Tribology, Theory Machine, TPM, Pinch Technology</li></ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('meta', 'Metallurgical &amp; Materials Engineering', '<p>The Department of <b> Metallurgical and Materials Engineering</b> was amongst the four branches with which the institute was initially launched in 1960,\r\nwith increasing focus on :\r\n<ul><li> Advanced Materials</li>\r\n<li> Composite Materials</li>\r\n<li> Nanotechnology</li></ul>\r\nand the R&amp;D work being carried out in these fields in the metallurgical sector, <b>Materials Engineering</b> was included in the curriculum of the department in 1995.</br><b><br>Regular Programmes offered by the Department:</b></br>The Department started offering U.G. Programme from 1960 and P.G. Programme from 1965. The Ph.D Programme was started from 2003. The current intake of U.G. and P.G. Programmes are 92 and 18 respectively.\r\n<br>\r\n<b></br>Part Time Programmes offered by the Department:</b></br>\r\nThe Part time Programme in P.G. has been offered since 1980, which has a current intake of 30 students. Part time Ph.D programme has been offered since 1965.</br><b><br>Future Plans of the Department:</b>\r\n<ul><li>To start new M.Tech. Courses in Material Technology.</li><li>To create ample facilities for research activities to attract more P.G. Students.</li></ul>\r\n</p><br/><b>Research/Textbook Publications during last five years:</b><ul><li>International Journals: 12</li>\r\n<li>Indian Journals: 06</li><li>International Conference: 10</li>\r\n<li>National Conference: 29</li>\r\n<li>Text Books(Articles): 03</li></ul></br><b>Contribution of the Department in last five years:</b><ul><li>Ph.D. Guidance: 10</li>\r\n<li>M.Tech Project Guidance: 15</li>\r\n<li>B.Tech. Project: 250</li>\r\n<li>Publications: More then 40</li></ul></br>\r\n<b>Collaborations (Industrial/Institutional) :</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>With industry:<ul><ul><li>Tata Steel</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>Tata Motors</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>Usha Martin Industries Ltd</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>R &amp; D, SAIL, Ranchi</li></ul>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n<li>With National Research Laboratories:<ul><ul><li>NML,Jamshedpur</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>DMRL,Hyderabad</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>BARC,Mumbai</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>R &amp; D, Tata Steel</li></ul></li></ul>\r\n<li>With Other Institutions:\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul><li>IIT, Kharagpur</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>NIT, Rourkela</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>NIFFT, Ranchi</li></ul>\r\n<ul><li>NIT, Durgapur</li></ul>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=MME03" class="pagelink"> Dr. Mahesh Kumar Agrawal</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374025(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374027<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:mkagrawal.met@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">mkagarwal.met@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p><b>The Department has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</b></p><ul><li>Thermodynamics &amp; Kinetics Laboratory\n</li><li>Extractive Metallurgy Laboratory (Ferrous)</li><li>Physical Metallurgy Laboratory\n</li><li>Heat Treatment laboratory\n</li><li>Material Testing Laboratory\n</li><li>Geology &amp; Mineral Benefication Laboratory\n</li><li>Non Ferrous Metallurgy &amp; Corrosion Laboratory</li><li>Manufacturing Laboratory</li><li>Analytical Laboratory</li>\n<li>Foundary Laboratory</li><li>Advance Materials Laboratory</li><li>Corrosion Laboratory</li><li>Met. Analysis Laboratory</li><li>Computational Laboratory</li><li>Workshop</li>\n</ul><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b> Major Laboratory Equipments :</b></p>\n<ul><li>Induction Furnace</li><li>Direct Electric Arc Furnace (50Kgs)</li><li>Indirect Electric Arc Furnace (25Kgs)</li><li>High Temperature Melting Furnaces</li><li>Tubular Melting Furnace</li><li>Reducibility Apparatus</li><li>S.E.M.</li><li>X-ray Diffractometer</li><li>50 Kg Forging Hammer</li><li>Diffrential Dilatometer</li><li>Shell Modeling Apparatus</li><li>Die Casting Machine</li><li>Resistance Melting Furnace</li><li>Thermo Lab Dilatometer</li><li>Power Hammer</li><li>Horizontal Tube Furnace</li><li>Electronic Moisture Balance</li><li>Roll Crusher</li><li>Universal Sand Testing Machine</li><li>Reicher T-Universal Microscope</li><li>Carbon Equivalent Meter</li>', '<p><b>Research Areas :</b></p><ul><li> Environment Management & Waste Utilisation</li><li> Energy conservation</li><li> Developments of new materials</li><li> Materials characterizations & NDT</li><li>Examine the effect of thermo-physical properties of additives on their dissolution in steelmaking baths</li><li>Iron Ore Fines</li><li>Iron & chromimum ore beneficiation</li><li>Corrosion Engineering</li><li>Steel Technology</li><li>Process Metallurgy of Iron &amp; Steel</li><li>Laddle Metallurgy</li><li>Physical Metallurgy</li><li>Transport Phenomenon</li><li>Pneumatic Process</li><li>Mechanical Metallurgy</li><li>Fracture, Fatigue &amp; Failure Analysis</li><li>Foundary Technology</li><li>Waste Management</li><li>Mineral Benefication</li><li>Metallic Glass</li></ul><p>\r\n<b>Thrust Area :</b></p><ul><li>	Waste Management</li><li> Energy Conservation & Characterization of Raw Materials</li><li>Nano  technology</li><li>Materials Sceince Engineering</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><b>Important Research Projects :</b></p><p><table cellspacing="10px" border="1" cellpadding="10px" align="center"><tr><td><b>Project Title</b></td><td><b>Sponsoring Agency</b></td><td><b>Amount Sanctioned (in Lacs).</b></td><td><b>Co-ordinators/Principal Investigator</b></td><td><b>Status</b></td></tr><tr><td>Advanced Metal Melting</td><td>MHRD</td><td>52.5</td><td>Dr. S. N. Sinha</td><td>Completed</td></tr><tr><td>Central Facility for Advance Melting</td><td>MHRD</td><td>5.0</td><td>Dr. S. N. Sinha, Dr. M. K. Agrawal</td><td>Completed</td></tr><tr><td>Central Facilities for HNDT and Stress-Strain Analysis</td><td>MHRD</td><td>7.5</td><td>Dr. S. N. Sinha, Dr. H. L. Yadav</td><td>Completed</td></tr><tr><td>Modernization of Geology Lab</td><td>MHRD</td><td>7.0</td><td>Dr. Ranjit Prasad</td><td>Completed</td></tr><tr><td>Investigation on the thermo-chemistry of the interaction of Chromite spinel and silica under different conditions</td><td>MHRD</td><td>18.5</td><td>Dr. S. N. Sinha, Dr. Ranjit Prasad</td><td>Completed</td></tr></table></p>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>UG program</b>:\r\n	<ol><li>4 year B.Tech (H) in Mettalurgical &amp; MaterialsEngineering</li></ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b><a href="../department/mtechmeta.php">PG programs</a></b>:\r\n	<ol><li>2 year M.Tech in Extractive Metallurgy</li>\r\n    	<li>2 year M.Tech in Foundry Technology</li>\r\n<li>2 year M.Tech in Iron &amp; Steel Technology</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>3 year Diploma <b>Certificate Course</b> for Tata Steel employees.\r\n<li><b>Ph.D programs</b>:\r\n	<ol><li>Iron and steel making</li><li>Physical Metallurgy</li><li>Corrosion Engineering</li><li>Material Science</li><li>Thermodynamics</li><li>Waste Management and Utilisation.</li></ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('physics', 'Physics', '<p>Department of Physics was established in 1960.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=PHY01" class="pagelink"> Prof. Yamuna Prasad Yadav</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374036(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374037<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:ypyadav.phy@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">ypyadav.phy@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The Department  has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</p><p>1.UG Lab.</p>\n	\n	<p>2.Photonics Lab.</p>\n	\n	<p>3.Microwave Lab.</p> ', '<p><b>Research areas</b>:</p> <ul><li>Nuclear Scattering</li><li> Holography</li><li> Solar Energy</li>', '<p>The Department offers the following courses: </p><ul><li><b>UG Program:</b></li></ul> Participating in the teaching of B. Tech. (Honours) course as a                  \n                   Supporting department    \n'),
('prod', 'Manufacturing Engineering', '<p>The department was established in the year 1988.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=MFE05" class="pagelink"> Dr. Raj Ballav </a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374129(HOD office),&nbsp;+91-657-2374133<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:rballav.prod@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">rballav.prod@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The Department has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</p><ul><li><p>Welding Lab</p></li><li>Non Traditional Manufacturing Lab</li><li>CAD/CAM Lab</li><li>Advanced Manufacturing Lab</li><li>Ergonomics Lab</li><li>Metal Forming Lab</li></ul>', '<p><b>Research Areas:</b></p><ul><li> Production Management</li><li> Production and Manufacturing Engineering</li><li> Robotics</li><li>Automation</li><li>CAD/ CAM</li><li>Management</li><li>Production</li><li>R.E and R.P with CAD application </li><li>Solar Energy</li><li>Energy Management</li><li>Machine Design</li><li>Production Engineering</li><li>Industrial Engineering</li></ul>', '<p>The department offers the following academic programs which have been designed in close interaction with industry and keeping in mind their current needs :-\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Manufacturing Engineering</li>\r\n<li>M.Tech. in Industrial &amp; Management Engineering</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>'),
('humanities', 'Humanities, Social Sciences and Management', '<p>The Deptartment was established in 1960.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=HUM01" class="pagelink"> Dr. Rajiv Bhushan</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374063<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:rbhushan.hum@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">rbhushan.hum@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>Not Available.</p>', '<p><b>Research Areas:</b></p><ul><li>American Literature</li><li>Business Communication</li><li>Feminist Narratology</li><li>Indian English </li><li>Women’s Fiction</li><li>Indian Women Short Fiction in English</li><li>Gender Studies and Sexual Studies</li><li>Indian English Poetry and Poetic Consciousness</li></ul>', '<p>The Department offers the following courses: </p><ul><li><b>UG Program:</b></li></ul> Participating in the teaching of B. Tech. (Honours) course as a                  \n                   Supporting department    \n');
