('civil', 'Civil Engineering', '<p>The Department of Civil Engineering of National Institute of Technology (formerly Regional Institute of Technology) Jamshedpur was started with the inception of the institute itself in 1960. This core department had sanctioned strength of two Professors, two Assistant Professors and nine Lecturers.</p>\r\n<p>Present intake capacity of 90 students in each batch. The department has well qualified and experienced faculty members. Apart from teaching and research, all faculties are actively involving in training and other extra curricular activities for all round development of the Department.</p>\r\n<p>Faculties of this department are also undertaking design, testing &amp; consultancy works for various organizations leading to resource generation for the Institute. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=102006" class="pagelink"> Dr. Anil Kumar Choudhary</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> + 91-657-2374123, 2374105<br />\r\n<b>Fax:</b> + 91-657-2373246<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto: hod.civil@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">hod.civil@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The department has following Laboratories:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Structural Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Concrete Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Soli Mechanics Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Geotechnical Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Transportation Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Survey Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n<li>CAD  Laboratory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The major equipments available are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>UTM 1500 KN</li>\r\n<li>Ultra Sonic Pulse Velocity</li>\r\n<li>Flexural Testing Machine</li>\r\n<li>CBR Set-up</li>\r\n<li>Shear Strength Test Apparatus</li>\r\n<li>Digital Tri-axial Set-up</li>\r\n<li>Permeability Test Set-up</li>\r\n<li>Gas Chromotograph</li>\r\n<li>Spectrophoto meter</li>\r\n<li>COD &amp; DO meter</li>\r\n<li>Respiratory Dust Sampler</li>\r\n<li>pH meter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Softwares:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>STRAP Suit Software Version 12.5</li>\r\n<li>PLAXIX 2D version 8.6</li>\r\n<li>Plax Flow version 1.4</li>\r\n<li>GGU Software (20 Users)</li>\r\n<li>GEO5  version 5.3 ( 5 Users)</li>\r\n<li>KANAL++ & Aqua ++</li>\r\n<li>CFX, SAP, ETABS, NASTRAN</li>\r\n<li>AUTODESK</li>\r\n<li>RAM</li>\r\n<li>AUTO-CAD</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Low cost Building materials\r\nPile Foundation</p>\r\n<p>Planning Management of Traffic Flow Pattern</p>\r\n<p>Slag Aggregate Cement Concrete</p>\r\n<p>Study on Reinforced Fly ash</p>\r\n<p>Design of Multistoried Structures</p>\r\n<p>Recycled Aggregate Concrete</p>\r\n<p>Water Quality Assessment</p>\r\n<p>Drinking Water supply network system development</p>\r\n<p>River Flood Flow Forecasting</p>\r\n<p>Earth Quake Impact Assessment\r\n</p>', '\r\n<p>The department offers the following academic programs which have been designed in close interaction with industry and keeping in mind their current needs :-\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Civil Engineering</li>\r\n<li>M.Tech. in Structural Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Ph.D. in relevant areas</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
('eee', 'Electrical &amp; Electronics Engg.', '<p>The Department of Electrical Engineering was started in 1960. The Department has been consistently producing quality Electrical Engineers since its inception  and is also involved in research and development activities.<br/>\r\nThe alumni of the department are well placed in both public and private sectors.<br/>\r\nIn addition to the UG program the department runs PG program in Power Systems and Ph.D. program in different areas of specialization.</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To be a centre for imparting world class education in the field of electrical engineering and conduct extensive and quality research and to propel innovations for the betterment of society.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To train young minds and to equip them with the best possible technical knowledge to meet the current and future demands of the industry, to recognize education and  research in close interaction with the industry and installing leadership qualities in  young men and women who enter the portals of the institute with sensitivity for social development and with an eye for growth in international perspective.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=105003" class="pagelink"> Prof. Amar Nath Thakur</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-6572374067 <br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="anthakur.ee@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">anthakur.ee@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>\r\n', '<p>Electrical Machine Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>Instrumentation and Measurement Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>Power System Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>Control System Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>Power Electronics Laboratory (U.G.)</p>\r\n<p>Power Electronics Laboratory (P.G.)</p>\r\n<p>Microprocessor Laboratory</p>\r\n<p>Computer Centre (Departmental)</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p style="text-align:justify;">The department offers the following course(s) :-\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Electrical &amp; Electronics Engg.</li>\r\n<li><a href="../department/mtecheee.php">M.Tech. in Power System</a></li>\r\n<li>Ph.D.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
('ece', 'Electronics &amp; Communication Engg.', '<p>\r\nDepartment of Electronics and communication Engineering was started in 1989. The department covers a host of subjects inclusive of electronic circuits, microprocessor, digital signal processing, analog communication, digital communication, mobile communication, VLSI, embedded systems, instrumentation ETC. The department has laboratories catering to all the subjects of studies. There are five research scholars working in different specializations under the groups Communication engineering, VLSI and embedded systems, Signal Processing, Instrumentation and soft computing. The Department has highly motivated faculty pool. \r\n</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Enhance the Student Learning Environment</li>\r\n<li>Commitment to Student Transformation and Success</li>\r\n<li>Transformational Scholarship</li>\r\n<li>Developing our Campus Community</li>\r\n<li>Resource Development</li>\r\n<li>Engagement with the Region</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Value creation through economic, social, and environmental development targeted to an increasing global and multicultural world.</li>\r\n<li>This leads an increasing number of academic and public service activities that involve and benefit the local community, the State of Jharkhand, India, and ultimately, the world. This continuing commitment to the public good, through a variety of outreach activities, is grounded in our tradition as a land-grant Institution.</li>\r\n<li>Original ideas that advance society through discovery, inquiry, innovation, research, transformational scholarship, and creative activities.</li>\r\n<li>Our ability to create value is dependent on discovering new knowledge and generating new ideas and expressions. The complex concerns of the 21st century cannot be addressed with existing knowledge and systems. Our aim is a dramatic increase in these activities, requiring the interaction between committed, diverse faculty, staff, students and community.</li>\r\n<li>Leadership through the preparation of capable and ethical leaders.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b> <a href="../faculty/index.php?id=106002" class="pagelink">Dr. Shiva Nand Singh</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone: </b>  <br />\r\n<b>Email: </b> <a href="mailto:snsingh.ece@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">snsingh.ece@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '\r\n<p>The department offers the following academic programs which have been designed in close interaction with industry and keeping in mind their current needs :-\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.Tech. (Hons.) in Civil Engineering</li>\r\n<li>M.Tech. in VLSI design in embedded system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
('maths', 'Mathematics', '<p>Details to be Updated Soon...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=108001" class="pagelink"> Dr. S. Jha</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374059<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto: sjha.math@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">sjha.math@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
('me', 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p>Department of Mechanical Engineering was established in 1960 with the inception of Institute.</p>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Vision</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To be a center of for imparting world class education in the field of Mechanical Engineering and conduct extensive and quality research and to propel innovations for the betterment of society.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span class="pagesubheading">Mission</span>\r\n<img src="../images/h2.png" width="100%" />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To train young minds and to equip them with the best possible technical knowledge to meet the current and future demands of the industry, to recognize education and research in close interaction with the industry and instilling leadership qualities in young men and women who enter the portals of the Institute with sensitivity for social development and with an eye for growth in international perspective.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=109010" class="pagelink"> Prof. (Dr.) R.K.Prasad</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374050 <br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:rkprasad.me@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">rkprasad.me@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>The Department  has following laboratories with latest equipment and software:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Applied  Thermodynamics Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>CAD, CAM  &amp; CFD Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Fluid  Mechanics and Fluid Machinery Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Heat  Transfer laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Dynamics of  Machinery Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Metrology  Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Strength  of Materials Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Thermodynamics Model Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Automobile  Engineering Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>Gas Dynamics  Laboratory</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p><b>Research areas</b>:</p>\r\n<ul><li>CFD, Heat Transfer, Solar Energy, Combined Power  Cycle, Gas Turbine, Tribology, Theory Machine, TPM, Pinch  Technology</li></ul>\r\n<p><b>Conference and Short Term courses organized</b>:</p>\r\n<ol><li>National  Conference on &ldquo;Modelling and Simulation of Heat Transfer and Fluid Flow&rdquo; was  organized during July 9-10,  2010.</li>\r\n	<li>Short Term  Training Program on &ldquo;Modelling and Simulation of Renewable Energy Systems&rdquo; was  organized during June18-22, 2012.</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>UG program</b>:\r\n	<ol><li>4 year B.Tech (H) in Mechanical Engineering</li></ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b><a href="../department/mtechmech.php">PG programs</a></b>:\r\n	<ol><li>2 year M.Tech in Computer Integrated Design and Manufacturing</li>\r\n    	<li>2 year M.Tech in Thermal and Fluids Engineering</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b>Ph.D programs</b>:\r\n	<ul><li>CFD, Heat Transfer, Solar Energy, Combined Power Cycle, Gas Turbine, Tribology, Theory Machine, TPM, Pinch Technology</li></ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
('meta', 'Metallurgical &amp; Materials Engineering', '<p>Details to be Updated Soon...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Head of the Department:</b><a href="../faculty/index.php?id=110003" class="pagelink"> Dr. MAHESH KUMAR AGARWAL</a><br />\r\n<b>Phone:</b> +91-657-2374036<br />\r\n<b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:mkagarwal.met@nitjsr.ac.in" class="pagelink">mkagarwal.met@nitjsr.ac.in</a></p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>', '<p>The department offers the following course(s) :-\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>UG program</b>:\r\n	<ol><li>4 year B.Tech (H) in Mettalurgical &amp; MaterialsEngineering</li></ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b><a href="../department/mtechmeta.php">PG programs</a></b>:\r\n	<ol><li>2 year M.Tech in Extractive Metallurgy</li>\r\n    	<li>2 year M.Tech in Foundry Technology</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><b>Ph.D programs</b>:\r\n	<ul><li>Iron and steel making, Physical Metallurgy, Corrosion Engineering, Material Science, Thermodynamics, Waste Management and Utilisation.</li></ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>To be Updated soon.</p>'),
