('CA10', 'Mr. Dindayal Mahto', '../faculty/images/ddm.jpg', 'Lecturer (on contract)', 'Computer Applications', 'Ph.D. (Pursuing), NIT Jamshedpur, Jharkhand \nM.Tech. (Information Security), BIT Mesra, Ranchi, Jharkhand\n \n\n\nMr. Dindayal Mahto joined the Institute in April 2011                                                                                                                                                         ', 'C-17, NIT Campus, Jamshedpur 831014                                                                                                                                                         ', '+91-657-2374115', '+91-9162712003', 'dindayalmahto.ca@nitjsr.ac.in', '<p><b>Professional Experience</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>Lecturer (on Contract), National Institute of Technology, Jamshedpur, JH, April-2011 to till date.</li><li>Sr. Technical Faculty, (Study Center of Kuvempu University, Shimoga), NIIT, Ranchi Center, Ranchi, JH, July-2006 to July-2010.</li><li>System Executive, SAMADHAN, Ranchi, Jharkhand, Aug-1998 to Jun-2003.</li></ol><p><b>Research Interest</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>Software Safety, Security and Reliability</li><li>Network Security and Cryptography</li><li>Database Security and Biometrics Security</li></ol><p><b>Certifications</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>MCTS: <b>Microsoft</b> Certified Technology Specialist (.Net Framework 2.0: Windows Application), ID: 6671604, 11/01/2009</li><li><b>IBM</b> Certified Academic Associate (DB2 9 Database and Application Fundamentals), 01/10/2010</li></ol><p><b>Courses Taught (UG Programme)</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>Programming in C, C++, Java, C#, VB.NET, ASP.NET</li><li>Oracle PL/SQL, Oracle Forms Developer, Crystal Reports</li><li>RDBMS (Oracle 9i, Ms. SQL Server 2005)</li><li>Data Structure, Algorithm, S/W Engineering,&nbsp;OOPs and OOAD</li></ol><p><b>Courses Teaching (UG &amp; PG Programme)</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>System Simulation &amp; Modelling (CA35114)</li><li>Decision Support Systems (CA34117)</li><li>DSS &amp; Simulation Lab. (CA35208)</li><li>Management Information Systems (GE1805)</li></ol><p><b>Additional Workload</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>MIS Administrator, NIT, Jamshedpur</li><li>Asst. Warden,&nbsp;Hostel H - Abul Kalam Hall Of Residence, NIT, Jamshedpur</li></ol><p><b>Member of Professional Body</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li><b>IACSIT</b> (International Association of Computer Science and Iinformation Technology), Member ID: 80344278</li><li><b>IAENG</b> (Internation Association of Engineers), Member ID: 120590</li><li><b>ACM-CSTA</b> (Computer Science Teachers Association), Member ID: 0192335</li></ol><p><b>International Conference / Journals</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li><b>Dindayal Mahto</b> and D.K. Yadav - Network Security using ECC with Biometric - , <em>in QSHINE 2013, proceeding of <b>Springer LNICST</b></em>, GBU, G. Noida, UP, 2013.</li></ol><p><b>Short Term Programmes/ Workshops Attended</b></p><ol start=\\"\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;1\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\&quot;\\"><li>Five (5) Days Refresher Course on Database Security, March 5-9 , 2012, Under Information Security Education Awareness Programme, Ministry of Communication and Information Technology, Govt of India, organized by Department of Computer Science and Engineering, National Institute of Technology, Warangal, A.P.</li><li>Indo-Australia Workshop on Optimization Techniques for Human Language Technology, (Supported by Australia India Strategic Research Fund, Round Six 2011/2012), IIT Patna, Bihar, December 16, 2012</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p>'),
('CE01', 'Prof. Ashok Kumar Khan', '../faculty/images/akce.JPG', 'Professor', 'Civil Engineering', '<b>Ph.D.</b> I.I.T. Kharagpur\n\n<b>Prof. A.K. Khan</b> joined the Institute in 1991                  ', 'Qtr No B-27, NIT Campus, NIT Jamshedpur                        ', '0657-2373860 (R)', '+91-9334800643', 'akkhan.ce@nitjsr.ac.in', '<p><b>Career History</b><br></p><ul><li>Professional Career:</li></ul><p>Since September,1976 to April,1989 actively associated as Senior Executives of various National Important Premier Construction Company to execute a good number of National/International important projects all over the country and abroad.</p><ul><li>Teaching &amp; Research:</li></ul><p>Since May,1989 till date actively involved in teaching and research in the premier Institute of India viz. IIT Khargapur, NIT Jamshedpur. The specialized subject of interests are Soil Duynamics, Environmental and Sustainable Development, Concrete Technology. Around twenty Post Graduate thesis supervised and one Ph.D scholar research work under progress.</p><ul><li>Administrative Experience:</li></ul><p>In addition to the teaching and research activities, administrative responsibilities in department and Institute level also satisfactorily performed. Institute earn a good amount of revenue through testing and consultancy under my leadership as Head of the Department.</p><p><b>Academic or Professional Award (Honors)</b>:</p><ul><li>Dinesh Mohar Biennial Prize for best paper published through Indian Geotechnical journal on Pile Foundation, 1994.</li><li>Appointed as reviewer of the book entitled- Ã¢â‚¬Å“Building MaterialsÃ¢â‚¬Â by M.L. Gambhir through Tata Mac-Graw Hills, Publisher.</li></ul><p><b>External Examiner/Visiting Professor for other University/Institute</b>:</p><ul><li>Regularly appointed as External Examiner/Visiting Professor for NIT Silchar, Assam and BIT Mesra, Ranchi, Jharkhand.</li></ul><p><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p><b>Member of the Professional bodies</b>:</p><ul><li>Member of Institute of Engineers</li><li>Life Fellow Member of Indian Geotechnical Society</li><li>Member of the International Society of Soil Mechanics and Foundation Engineering</li><li>Life Member of Indian Road Congress</li><li>Member of the National Board of Accreditation Committee</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><b>Publications</b></p><p>Thirty nos. of technical research paper published in National/International Journals and Conferences in the field of Geotechnical Engineering, Concrete Technology, Environmental &nbsp;Engg. And Traffic &amp; Transportation Engg.</p>'),
